Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of various algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper uses numerical methods and algorithms to compute the constrained minimal singular value, which is a topic in numerical analysis. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the properties of subgaussian ensembles, which is a topic in probability theory and statistics. Hence, cs.SI (Statistics) is also a possible sub-category.
